title: North Macedonia House Price Index
description: Housing Index in Macedonia increased to 128.34 points in the third quarter of 2022 from 122.56 points in the second quarter of 2022. Housing Index in Macedonia averaged 89.51 points from 2000 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 128.34 points in the third quarter of 2022 and a record low of 56.68 points in the first quarter of 2000. This page provides - Macedonia Housing Index- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: National Bank of the Republic of Macedonia
